 ago.  <br>
After a few hours, she completed her rounds.  The forest perimiter and there were no signs of intruders or...Centaurs.  The turned Monsoon back home and rode into her peaceful village.::: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/spinningsword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#993300>(12/1/00 4:59:12 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Hippolyte?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A peaceful village far from the war</span><hr size=1> :::Hipp rides Monsoon into the village that is now stirring with the usual domestic rituals.  She smiles and nods to those she rides slowely past...and then arrives to the stables and pasture.  She hops off her mare, removes the tack, and then releases Monsoon into the pasture to enjoy the green grass.  After the Queen returns the tack to it's proper places.  She begins to roam the village.  She then comes upon the pavilion.  There she finds Terrayus teaching the young girls to skills of fighting.  The young warriors move in a Kata.  Their arms moving in fluid motion, like a small sea stirring.  Hipp stops near a post that holds up the pavilion and watches:::<br>
<Center><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/hipplistens1.jpg></Center><br>
